<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Log off / Sign out button suddenly removed by Group Poli]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=8108&amp;p=34748#p34748"><![CDATA[
Never mind, for some reason <strong>StartMenuLogOff </strong>had been set to 1 in the registry, under the key <br /><strong>HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Policies\Explorer</strong><br /><br />I found the solution here:<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://answers.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/forum/windows_7-desktop/remove-windows-7-log-off-button/d91eaee9-5c8f-4c03-a19b-e7885c04b57c?auth=1">https://answers.microsoft.com/en-us/win ... 57c?auth=1</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Probably some other stupid 'tweak' software did it.<br /><br />Thanks again for Classic Shell, wouldn't know how I would do without it.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=27191">Pathduck</a> — Tue Nov 21, 2017 3:58 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
