<title type="html"><![CDATA[Log off / Sign out button suddenly removed by Group Policy?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=8108&amp;p=34747#p34747"><![CDATA[
Hi, I've been using CSM for years now, can't live without it and hopefull it will work for some years still.<br /><br />However, just today I noticed the Log Off button gone from the Start Menu - I use the &quot;Classic Style&quot; so would expect to find it right above Shutdown. <br /><br />In the CSM settings I find this:<br /><br /><img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/download/file.php?mode=view&amp;id=5079&amp;sid=a808acea8d2e642e2c0bafe3b3d9cd43" alt="" /><br /><br />So a group policy suddenly triggered this? But which one?<br /><br />System is Win10 Pro x64 and I have Gpedit so I've looked around to find some setting that might've changed - nothing. Very confusing <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_sad.gif" alt=":(" title="Sad" /> <br /><br />I updated to Fall Creators Update about a week ago, but didn't notice this until now, so not even sure the update caused it to go away or something else the last days might have caused it <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_neutral.gif" alt=":|" title="Neutral" /><br /><br />I am even considering rolling back to the backup I did a couple of days ago just to check whether the same issue was there then, but I think I would have noticed it.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=27191">Pathduck</a> — Mon Nov 20, 2017 3:06 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
